OL,4,Creadings ahead of latest energy price
OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FMore than seven million households
OL,8,Fstill on a standard energy tariff have
OL,9,Fbeen urged to send in meter readings
OL,10,Fto avoid paying higher prices from
OL,11,FOctober 1.
OL,13,FThe energy price cap will rise by 2%
OL,14,Ffrom Wednesday for a typical household
OL,15,Fin England, Scotland and Wales, just
OL,16,Fas cooler temperatures see many
OL,17,Fswitching on their central heating.
