OL,4,Creadings ahead of latest energy price
OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FUswitch energy spokesman Ben Gallizzi
OL,8,Fsaid: "Households should take a moment
OL,9,Fto read their energy meter in the
OL,10,Fcoming days to avoid the possibility
OL,11,Fof being charged at October's higher
OL,12,Fenergy rates.
OL,14,F"Customers who don't have a smart
OL,15,Fmeter should submit their readings
OL,16,Fbefore or on Wednesday October 1, so
OL,17,Ftheir supplier has an updated ` and
OL,18,Faccurate ` view of their account.
