OL,5,Crise
OL,7,F"Energy billpayers can get ahead of
OL,8,FOctober's price hike by fixing at
OL,9,Fcheaper rates now. Currently, there
OL,10,Fare a range of fixed deals currently
OL,11,Favailable that are around #215 cheaper
OL,12,Fthan the October price cap for the
OL,13,Faverage household.
OL,15,F"If you can switch to a deal cheaper
OL,16,Fthan the October price cap, now is a
OL,17,Fgood time to make the change. We urge
OL,18,Fcustomers to run an energy comparison
OL,19,Fas soon as possible."
