OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FThe increase in energy costs come
OL,8,Fdespite wholesale prices falling by 2%
OL,9,Fover the three months prior to Ofgem's
OL,10,Flatest price cap decision.
OL,12,FHowever, standing charges ` the figure
OL,13,Fconsumers pay per day to have energy
OL,14,Fsupplied to their homes ` are set to
OL,15,Frise by 4% for electricity and 14% for
OL,16,Fgas, or 7p a day, primarily driven by
OL,17,Fthe Government's expansion of the Warm
OL,18,FHome Discount.
