OL,7,FThe energy price cap was introduced by
OL,8,Fthe government in January 2019 and
OL,9,Fsets a maximum price that energy
OL,10,Fsuppliers can charge consumers in
OL,11,FEngland, Scotland and Wales for each
OL,12,Fkilowatt hour (kWh) of energy they use.
OL,14,FIt does not limit total bills because
OL,15,Fhouseholders still pay for the amount
OL,16,Fof energy they consume.
